<p>On all my tables I have an IsDeleted field so that I can toggle records on and off. I'm trying to figure out how to use LinqToSql to filter out deleted records in the join table but I don't know how to identify that table in the linq query. Here is my basic table definition:</p>  <pre><code>    modelBuilder.Entity&lt;MenuItemsEntity&gt;().ToTable("MenuItems")     .HasMany(m =&gt; m.UserGroups).WithMany(ur =&gt; ur.MenuItems)     .Map(m =&gt;     {         m.ToTable("MenuItems_UserGroups")             .MapLeftKey("MenuItemId")             .MapRightKey("UserGroupId");     }); </code></pre>  <p>and here is my linq statement so far:</p>  <pre><code>var menuItems = _ctx.MenuItems.Where(x =&gt; !x.IsDeleted &amp;&amp; x.ParentId == parentId  &amp;&amp; x.UserGroups.Any(r =&gt; !r.IsDeleted &amp;&amp; r.Id == userGroupId)); </code></pre>  <p>This adds the IsDeleted check for tables MenuItems and UserGroups, but not for MenuItems_UserGroups. </p>  <p>Any ideas?</p>